devdoc.author: Julien Niset - <julien@argent.im>
devdoc.details: Implementation of an ENS manager that orchestrates the complete registration of subdomains for a single root (e.g. argent.eth). The contract defines a manager role who is the only role that can trigger the registration of a new subdomain.

changeENSResolver(address).details: Lets the owner change the address of the ENS resolver contract.

params._ensResolver: The address of the ENS resolver contract.

changeOwner(address).details: Lets the owner transfer ownership of the contract to a new owner.

changeRootnodeOwner(address).details: This function must be called when the ENS Manager contract is replaced and the address of the new Manager should be provided.

params._newOwner: The address of the new ENS manager that will manage the root node.

constructor.details: Constructor that sets the ENS root name and root node to manage.

params._ensRegistry: The address of the ENS registry
params._ensResolver: The address of the ENS resolver
params._rootNode: The node of the root name (e.g. namehash(argentx.eth)).

getENSReverseRegistrar().details: Gets the official ENS reverse registrar.
getENSReverseRegistrar().return: Address of the ENS reverse registrar.

isAvailable(bytes32).details: Returns true is a given subnode is available.
isAvailable(bytes32).return: true if the subnode is available.

register(string,address).details: Lets the manager assign an ENS subdomain of the root node to a target address. Registers both the forward and reverse ENS.
